Certainly! Drafting a clear and structured payload contract for clinician alerts is crucial for ensuring that all necessary information is conveyed effectively. Below is an example of a JSON schema for the clinician alert payload contract:

### Clinician Alert Payload Contract

#### Schema Definition

```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema",
  "$id": "https://example.com/cds-alert-payload.json",
  "title": "CDS Alert Payload",
  "description": "Payload contract for clinician alerts generated by the CDS API.",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "patient_id": {
      "description": "The unique identifier of the patient.",
      "type": "string"
    },
    "alert_id": {
      "description": "A unique identifier for this alert instance.",
      "type": "string"
    },
    "severity_level": {
      "description": "The severity level of the alert (INFO, WARNING, CRITICAL).",
      "type": "string",
      "enum": ["INFO", "WARNING", "CRITICAL"]
    },
    "timestamp": {
      "description": "Timestamp when the alert was generated.",
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time"
    },
    "message": {
      "description": "A brief message describing the alert.",
      "type": "string"
    },
    "recommendation": {
      "description": "Recommended action based on the alert.",
      "type": "string"
    },
    "evidence_references": {
      "description": "List of clinical guideline citations supporting the recommendation.",
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "url": {
            "description": "URL to the evidence reference (clinical guideline, study, etc.).",
            "type": "string"
          },
          "title": {
            "description": "Title of the evidence reference.",
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "required": ["url", "title"]
      }
    },
    "context": {
      "description": "Additional context or data related to the alert (e.g., vital signs, lab results).",
      "type": "object"
    }
  },
  "required": [
    "patient_id",
    "alert_id",
    "severity_level",
    "timestamp",
    "message",
    "recommendation",
    "evidence_references"
  ]
}
```

#### Example Payload

Here’s an example of how a clinician alert payload might look based on the schema:

```json
{
  "patient_id": "1234567890",
  "alert_id": "ALERT-12345",
  "severity_level": "CRITICAL",
  "timestamp": "2023-10-05T14:30:00Z",
  "message": "Critical oxygen saturation level detected.",
  "recommendation": "Administer supplemental oxygen immediately.",
  "evidence_references": [
    {
      "url": "https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/volumes/65/wr/pdfs/wrw121516a4.pdf",
      "title": "CDC Guidelines for Oxygen Therapy"
    }
  ],
  "context": {
    "vitals": [
      {
        "code": "http://loinc.org|29463-7",
        "valueQuantity": {
          "value": 80,
          "unit": "%"
        },
        "effectiveDateTime": "2023-10-05T14:29:00Z"
      }
    ],
    "lab_results": [
      {
        "code": "http://loinc.org|26014-8",
        "valueQuantity": {
          "value": 1.2,
          "unit": "mg/dL"
        },
        "effectiveDateTime": "2023-10-05T14:28:00Z"
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

### Explanation

#### Key Fields
- **patient_id**: Unique identifier of the patient.
- **alert_id**: A unique identifier for this alert instance to avoid duplicate alerts.
- **severity_level**: Indicates the severity level (INFO, WARNING, CRITICAL).
- **timestamp**: Timestamp when the alert was generated.
- **message**: Brief message describing the alert.
- **recommendation**: Recommended action based on the alert.
- **evidence_references**: List of clinical guideline citations supporting the recommendation.

#### Context
The `context` field can include additional relevant data such as vital signs and lab results that provide more context to the clinician. This helps in making informed decisions based on real-time patient data.

### Usage

This schema ensures consistency and completeness in alert payloads, making it easier for clinicians to understand and act upon alerts generated by your CDS system. It also facilitates integration with other systems and tools that consume these alerts.

Feel free to adjust the schema as needed to fit specific requirements or additional fields you might need!

